<pb facs="liv_000019_0758" n="0758"/>
<lb/><fw n="758"><add place="margintop" rend="gray left" hand="#U">758</add></fw>
<lb/><p>Despatch <choice><abbr>N<hi rend="sup">o</hi></abbr><expan>Number</expan></choice> 4 to <persName>Earl Granville</persName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10"><hi rend="double-underline">October</hi></date></seg> <!-- Adrian, should the name of the recipient be in the bibl tag? HB --><!-- Also, I am unsure of the year at the moment so only dating it based on next line's date of the Despatch. HB --><!-- from the previous section I had the year as 1868 but the despatches are 1871, ks -->
<lb/>dated <placeName><settlement type="town">Ujiji</settlement></placeName> <date when="1871-12-18">18 December 1871</date> <seg rend="right"><date from="1871-10-17" to="1871-10-21">17-18-21-</date></seg>
<lb/><choice><abbr>P.S</abbr><expan>Post Script</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>D<hi rend="sup">o</hi></abbr><expan>Ditto</expan></choice> ask for vaccine virus <seg rend="right"><unclear cert="low"><date when="1871-10-21">21</date></unclear></seg><!-- really unsure about the date, on the previous page I was heading towards the end of september 1868, but i wiz so confused as to the correct year i'm disinclined to arbitrarily change all your dates :-) ks --><!-- changed my mind am changing your dates :-)-->
<lb/><bibl>Journal</bibl> continued - from <date when="1871-09-17">17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Sept.</abbr><expan>September</expan></choice></date> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-21">21</date></seg> <!-- Again, check the year's on this once integrated. HB -->
<lb/>Clearances of forest - <term type="animal">Parrots</term> nest <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-21">—</date></seg>
<lb/>and <term type="plant">Binayoba</term> huts on lofty trees <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-21">—</date></seg>
<lb/>Leave <placeName><settlement type="town">Bambarre</settlement></placeName> and go Due North <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-21">—</date></seg>
<lb/>cross <placeName><geogName type="river">Luamo</geogName></placeName> - a loving couple <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-21">—</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><term type="animal">Elephant</term> traps in Forest - <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-22">22</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p>Man supposed to have been eaten - <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-23">23</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><seg type="weather">Frequent drenchings by rains &amp; dew</seg> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-21">—</date></seg>
<lb/>uproarious villagers - dense forest <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-21">—</date></seg>
<lb/>the <placeName><geogName><choice><abbr>R</abbr><expan>River</expan></choice> Lolinde</geogName></placeName> - <term type="plant"><foreign xml:lang="und">Muale</foreign> palm</term> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-23">—</date></seg>
<lb/><foreign xml:lang="und"><term type="plant">Tikatika</term></foreign> or <foreign xml:lang="und"><term type="plant">Kintefwetefwe</term></foreign> a living <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-23">—</date></seg>
<lb/><term type="plant_foodstuff">vegetable</term> bridge - <term type="ailment">Choleraic</term> symptoms <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-23">—</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><term type="ailment">Leprous</term> hands but a kind heart <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-24">24.</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p>Turn <choice><abbr>S.W.</abbr><expan>South West</expan></choice> caught in the <seg type="weather">rain</seg> a <term type="animal">tree frog</term> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-25">25.</date></seg>
<lb/>very musical - Went to <placeName><settlement type="village">Mamohela</settlement></placeName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-25">—</date></seg> <!-- Not sure what Mamohela is as Katomba's camp...village? region? Left as just placeName for now. HB --><!-- and i went for village :-) -->
<lb/><persName>Katomba</persName>'s camp - <term type="tribe"><unclear cert="medium">Wachogone</unclear> tribe</term><!-- He's misspelt the tribe, Wachiogoné and only mentions them in 1870, ks --> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-25">—</date></seg>
<lb/><seg type="weather">Simoom</seg> in <placeName><country>Oman</country></placeName> - three tusked <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-25">—</date></seg> <!-- I'm pretty sure the second reading is the correct one, but wanted to cover it as a name in case the "in" was supposed to be "im" or part of a name - feel free to delete if we're certain it's the country :) HB --><!-- Its a wind dearest (muppet!), ks -->
<lb/><term type="animal">elephant</term> killed - 40 <term type="tribe">Manyema</term> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-25">—</date></seg>
<lb/>killed for one string of beads - <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-26">26</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><orgName><placeName><settlement type="city">Nassick</settlement></placeName> pupils</orgName> refuse all work <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-27">27</date></seg>
<lb/>Depart <choice><abbr>NW</abbr><expan>Northwest</expan></choice> with 3 <term type="occupation">attendants</term> only <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-27">—</date></seg>
<lb/><term type="insect">Driver ants</term> - <term type="occupation">Trader</term> assassinated <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-27">—</date></seg>
<lb/>by night - <choice><orig>shewed</orig><corr>showed</corr></choice> reaction against <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-27">—</date></seg>
<lb/>the bloody <orgName>Ujijians</orgName><!-- I've been marking the Ujijians as tribe, oops the previous section will be wrong then, ks --> <orgName>slaving</orgName> - the <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-27">—</date></seg>
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="river">Lualaba</geogName></placeName> not in the <placeName><region><choice><abbr>N.W.</abbr><expan>North West</expan></choice></region></placeName> feet <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-27">—</date></seg>
<lb/>torn and bleeding <term type="ailment">intractable sores</term> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-27">—</date></seg>
<lb/><orgName><term type="faith">Christian</term> boys</orgName> from <placeName><settlement type="city">Nassick</settlement></placeName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-27">—</date></seg>
<lb/>school eager <term type="occupation"><orgName>slave</orgName> hunters</term> if not <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-27">—</date></seg>
<lb/>in danger - Characters given to <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-27">—</date></seg>
<lb/>them by masters a public fraud <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-28">28</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p>Back to <placeName><settlement type="town">Bambarre</settlement></placeName> - <term type="ailment">Irritable <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-28">—</date></seg>
<lb/>eating ulcers</term> - <foreign xml:lang="und"><term type="ailment">Safura</term></foreign> or <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-29">29.</date></seg>
<lb/><unclear cert="medium"><term type="ailment">earth eating</term></unclear> a disease <hi rend="underline">per se</hi> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-29">—</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p>Deaths from broken hearts <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-29">—</date></seg>
<lb/>a strange complaint! <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10">October</date></seg></p>


<pb facs="liv_000019_0759" n="0759"/>
<lb/><fw n="759"><add place="margintop" rend="gray right" hand="#U">759</add></fw>
<lb/><p><date when="1871">1871</date> <orgName>slaves</orgName> of <orgName>Banians</orgName> arrive after <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10"><hi rend="double-underline">October</hi></date></seg>
<lb/>sixteen months rioting on my goods
<lb/>and at once mutiny - free swearing <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-30">30.</date></seg>
<lb/><term type="occupation">Headmen</term> remain at <placeName><settlement type="town">Ujiji</settlement></placeName> - <orgName>Banian</orgName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-31">31</date></seg>
<lb/>hatred of my presence &amp; disclosures <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-31">—</date></seg>
<lb/>of their <orgName>slaving</orgName> equal to that of <orgName>Arabs</orgName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-31">—</date></seg>
<lb/>but they use low cunning &amp; lying <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-31">—</date></seg>
<lb/>North to <placeName><geogName type="river">Luamo</geogName></placeName> again with <orgName>slaves</orgName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-31">—</date></seg>
<lb/><choice><sic>Recieve</sic><corr>Receive</corr></choice> a young <foreign xml:lang="und"><term type="animal">soko</term></foreign> at <placeName><settlement type="village">Mamohela</settlement></placeName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-31">—</date></seg>
<lb/>the least mischievous of all <term type="animal">monkeys</term> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-31">—</date></seg>
<lb/>very ugly - but have good characters <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-10-31">—</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><bibl>Private Memoranda</bibl> - <persName>Prince Albert</persName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11"><hi rend="double-underline">November</hi></date></seg>
<lb/>the <term type="nationality">Portuguese</term> rights tenderly cared for <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-01">1</date></seg>
<lb/>the <orgName>native</orgName> rights ignored - contrast <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-02">2</date></seg>
<lb/>presented by good <persName>Lord Palmerston</persName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-02">—</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><bibl>Private <choice><abbr>Mem.</abbr><expan>Memorandum</expan></choice></bibl> : <persName>John Moffat</persName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-03">3</date></seg>
<lb/>a mistake - <term type="occupation">missionaries</term> but <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-03">—</date></seg>
<lb/>men and not always very honest ones <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-03">—</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><bibl>Private <choice><abbr>Mem.</abbr><expan>Memorandum</expan></choice></bibl> of two <orgName><term type="tribe">Makololo</term></orgName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-04">4</date></seg>
<lb/><orgName><term type="occupation">missionaries</term></orgName> <persName>Helmore</persName> &amp; <persName>Price</persName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-04">—</date></seg> <!-- I couldn't split the orgName tag encapsulating Makololo missionaries, so put as two separate ones til a better plan devised. HB -->
<lb/>one a good man the other a born fool <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-04">—</date></seg>
<lb/><bibl>Private <choice><abbr>Mem.</abbr><expan>Memorandum</expan></choice></bibl> <persName>Thomas Baines</persName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-04">—</date></seg>
<lb/>a <term type="occupation">thief</term> and moral idiot <term type="occupation">artist</term> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-04">—</date></seg> <!-- Not sure if artist and thief warrant occupation tags in this humorous little tidbit :) HB --><!-- technically they are occupations :-) -->
<lb/>whose paintings are all caricatures <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-05">5.</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><persName><term type="occupation">Mayor</term> Sicard</persName> - 24 boxes of <term type="animal"><term type="foodstuff">sardines</term></term>
<lb/>he pocketed a very small matter! <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-06">6.</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p>Forgery - a wise one sided <term type="occupation">Attorney <choice><abbr>Gen<hi rend="sup">l</hi></abbr><expan>General</expan></choice></term> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-06">—</date></seg> <!-- Again, I cannot cross items with the persName tag, so putting around both words for now. HB -->
<lb/><persName>Baines</persName> bamboozles the <placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName> people <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-07">7</date></seg>
<lb/>and was helped to go to <placeName><geogName type="falls"><persName>Victoria</persName> falls</geogName></placeName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-07">—</date></seg>
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="cape">Cape</geogName></placeName> Paper vituperation like <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-08">8</date></seg> <!-- Not sure if this is a specific cape name, and if it's in fact Paper? HB -->
<lb/>blowing Penny trumpets <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-08">—</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><bibl>Private <choice><abbr>Mem.</abbr><expan>Memorandum</expan></choice></bibl> <persName><term type="occupation">Bishop</term> <w>Mac-<seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-08">—</date></seg> <!-- Bishop Mackenzie split over two lines is problematic - cannot use w tag on first line, so have left in the second but we need to finesse this one better. HB --><!-- seems to work though?, ks -->
<lb break="no"/>-kenzie</w></persName>'s mission <space extent="3" unit="words"/><seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-08">—</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><term type="tribe">Makololo</term> black<choice><sic>gaurded</sic><corr>guarded</corr></choice> for doing <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-08">—</date></seg>
<lb/>what they first began to do under <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-09">9</date></seg>
<lb/><term type="faith">episcopal</term> and clerical <w>leader- <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-09">—</date></seg>
<lb break="no"/>-ship</w> - Nil teaching nullified <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-10">10</date></seg>
<lb/>by my abandoning those who were <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-10">—</date></seg> <!-- Not sure if Nil needs to be tagged/what it is across this and the next line? HB --><!-- I haven't a scooby what it is, ks -->
<lb/>harboured by the Nil <term type="occupation">teachers</term> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-10">—</date></seg></p>


<pb facs="liv_000019_0760" n="0760"/>
<lb/><fw n="760"><add place="margintop" rend="gray left" hand="#U">760</add></fw>
<lb/><p><bibl>Private <choice><abbr>Mem.</abbr><expan>Memorandum</expan></choice></bibl> <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Tozer</persName> repudiates <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11"><hi rend="double-underline">November</hi></date></seg>
<lb/><persName><term type="occupation"><choice><abbr>bp</abbr><expan>Bishop</expan></choice></term> Mackenzie</persName> and the pugilistic <term type="occupation">bishop</term> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-11">11.</date></seg>
<lb/>is a man of peace - propagates a <seg rend="right"><date when="1871"></date></seg>
<lb/><term type="nationality">Portuguese</term> scandal &amp; <persName><term type="occupation"><choice><abbr>bp</abbr><expan>Bishop</expan></choice></term> Gray</persName> hides it <seg rend="right"><date when="1871"></date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><bibl>Private <choice><abbr>Mem.</abbr><expan>Memorandum</expan></choice></bibl> <persName>Richard Thornton</persName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-12">12.</date></seg>
<lb/>oh if he had a friend! and £12 bill <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-12">—</date></seg>
<lb/>for <term type="foodstuff">gin</term> came into <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> <choice><abbr>L</abbr><expan>Livingstone</expan></choice></persName>'s hands <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-12">—</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p>Retrospect of <choice><sic>carreer</sic><corr>career</corr></choice> at <placeName><settlement type="village">Kolobeng</settlement></placeName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-13">13.</date></seg>
<lb/>regret not playing with my children <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-13">—</date></seg>
<lb/>and being somewhat severe in <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-13">—</date></seg>
<lb/>following <choice><sic><persName>Solomons</persName></sic><corr><persName>Solomon</persName>'s</corr></choice> advice <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-13">—</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p><term type="tribe">Manyema</term> <orgName>cannibalism</orgName> - <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-14">14.</date></seg>
<lb/>Doubts a depraved taste the cause <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-14">—</date></seg>
<lb/>flesh saltish - stealing dead bodies <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-14">—</date></seg> <!-- I am tempted to tag bodies as foodstuff, but thought it would be in poor taste...get it?!?! TASTE!! Okay, I'm obviously up too late while coding haha :c) HB --><!-- Loon! :-) -->
<lb/>to eat the meat - practice stopped <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-14">—</date></seg>
<lb/>murders - a grandmother offered <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-14">—</date></seg>
<lb/>as a substitute - <foreign xml:lang="und"><term type="animal">soko</term></foreign> not so bad <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-14">—</date></seg>
<lb/>as men - <persName>Moenemokaia</persName> opinion <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-15">15</date></seg> <!-- Not sure if this is a person or tribe? HB --><!-- It is a person, the date is really annoying me, now i'm wondering whether its not my 1869 or your 187 but in fact 1871? ks  -->
<lb/>on qualification for travelling <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-15">—</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p>Leave <placeName><settlement type="village">Mamohela</settlement></placeName> - <placeName><settlement type="village">Basilañge</settlement></placeName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-16">16</date></seg>
<lb/>Direction of streets - morning - <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-16">—</date></seg>
<lb/>with families - beautiful scenes <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-16">—</date></seg>
<lb/>villages deserted in fear - iron <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-16">—</date></seg>
<lb/>bracelets out of fashion by beads <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-16">—</date></seg>
<lb/><orgName>slaves</orgName> mischief makers - <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-17">17</date></seg></p>
<lb/><p>Beauty of women - Forges at <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-17">—</date></seg>
<lb/>work <space extent="3" unit="chars"/>slippery paths - <persName>Kimazi</persName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-18">18</date></seg>
<lb/>a <term type="occupation">queen</term> for beauty - <term type="tribe">Mangara</term> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-18">—</date></seg> <!-- Again, could not split persName tag across two lines. HB --><!-- not needed, ks -->
<lb/><persName>Kasonga</persName> the <term type="occupation">chief</term> - Southing <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-18">—</date></seg>
<lb/>of <placeName><geogName type="river">Lualaba</geogName></placeName> - mighty river <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-18">—</date></seg>
<lb/><orgName><orgName>Arab</orgName><term type="occupation">trading agents</term></orgName> of <orgName>Banians</orgName> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-18">—</date></seg>
<lb/>Noisy <orgName>Arab</orgName> <term type="occupation">demagogue</term> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-18">18</date></seg>
<lb/><persName>Hassani</persName>'s trap of 25 bracelets <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-19">19</date></seg>
<lb/><persName>Kasonga</persName> never lies he says <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-20">20</date></seg>
<lb/><persName>Muhamad</persName> the <term type="occupation"><choice><sic>prophets</sic><corr>prophet's</corr></choice></term> <w>false<supplied>-</supplied></w> <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-20">—</date></seg>
<lb/><w>ness</w> copied &amp; propagated <seg rend="right"><date when="1871-11-20">—</date></seg>
